text: I'm sorry, but this looks so cliche and pretentious. I know a bit about the Chilean Mining Disaster and I get how it at least ends on a happy, somewhat inspiring note. But this trailer just gives off cheesy and corny vibes. The song is absolutely wrong for this, even if the lyrics may make sense, it doesn't fit the tone nor correlate with what's going on in the trailer. Not to mention that almost none of the leading actors in this film are actually from Chile which explains the horrible accents. Plus, adding Antonio Banderas at the forefront of all this makes this true story seem less convincing. I'm not saying it's going to be complete shit, however, I can't seem to have much nice things to say about this and I know it's just a trailer and that the movie hasn't been released yet, so I shouldn't judge. But I'm really just basing my opinion on the trailer alone.
